    {
      "id": "1914750c-f3ba-80df-9df1-c6e8ea83ca4d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Paper proposes a GA that minimizes a two-objective objective function: inter-group homogeneity (fairness) and intra-group homogeneity (low gap). Experiments on generated data show that the algorithm is efficient at generating groups. Moreover, the approach seems better than other alternatives at fulfilling the objectives functions - with uniform corssover based on random keys also being the most effective form of crossover operators. ",
